{"id":"datalinq-general-loops","name":null,"description":null,"code":"<div class=\"navbar\">\r\n  <div class=\"title\" id=\"function-title\"><a href=\"https://localhost:7277/datalinq/report/datalinq-guide@select-all-users@index\">DataLinq: Loops</a></div>\r\n  <div style=\"width: 30px;\"></div> \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"wrapper\">\r\n\r\n@{\r\n    List<string> list = new List<string>() {\"one\",\"two\",\"three\",\"four\",\"five\",\"six\",\"seven\",\"eight\",\"nine\",\"ten\"};\r\n}\r\n\r\n<button class=\"collapsible\">\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-label\">For loop</span>\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-actions\">\r\n<span class=\"action-button\" onclick=\"openPopup(event, 'loops_for')\">Code/Query</span>\r\n</span>\r\n</button>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n    <h1>For loop with count</h1>\r\n    @for (int i = 0; i < list.Count; i++)\r\n    {\r\n        <p>@list[i]</p>\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    <br/><h1>For loop with limit</h1>\r\n    @for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)\r\n    {\r\n        <p>@list[i]</p>\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    <br/><h1>For loop reversed</h1>\r\n    @for (int i = list.Count - 1; i >= 0; i--)\r\n    {\r\n        <p>@list[i]</p>\r\n    }\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"description_loops_for\" hidden>\r\nde: Mit einer for-Schleife kannst du eine Liste durchlaufen – entweder komplett (list.Count), begrenzt (z. B. nur 5 Elemente) oder rückwärts (list.Count - 1 bis 0).\r\nen: A for loop allows you to iterate over a list – either fully (list.Count), with a limit (e.g., only 5 items), or in reverse (list.Count - 1 to 0).\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"csharp_loops_for\" hidden><script type=\"text/plain\">\r\n@@{\r\n    List<string> list = new List<string>() {\"one\",\"two\",\"three\",\"four\",\"five\",\"six\",\"seven\",\"eight\",\"nine\",\"ten\"};\r\n}\r\n\r\n<h1>For loop with count</h1>\r\n@@for (int i = 0; i < list.Count; i++)\r\n{\r\n    <p>@@list[i]</p>\r\n}\r\n\r\n<br/><h1>For loop with limit</h1>\r\n@@for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)\r\n{\r\n    <p>@@list[i]</p>\r\n}\r\n\r\n<br/><h1>For loop reversed</h1>\r\n@@for (int i = list.Count - 1; i >= 0; i--)\r\n{\r\n    <p>@@list[i]</p>\r\n}\r\n</script></div>\r\n<div id=\"sql_loops_for\" hidden></div>\r\n\r\n<button class=\"collapsible\">\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-label\">Foreach loop</span>\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-actions\">\r\n<span class=\"action-button\" onclick=\"openPopup(event, 'loops_foreach')\">Code/Query</span>\r\n</span>\r\n</button>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n    @foreach(var number in list)\r\n    {\r\n        <p>@number</p>\r\n    }\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"description_loops_foreach\" hidden>\r\nde: Eine foreach-Schleife geht automatisch durch alle Elemente in einer Liste und speichert jedes Element nacheinander in einer eigenen Variable.\r\nen: A foreach loop automatically iterates over all elements in a list, storing each item one by one in its own variable.\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"csharp_loops_foreach\" hidden><script type=\"text/plain\">\r\n@@{\r\n    List<string> list = new List<string>() {\"one\",\"two\",\"three\",\"four\",\"five\",\"six\",\"seven\",\"eight\",\"nine\",\"ten\"};\r\n}\r\n\r\n@@foreach(var number in list)\r\n{\r\n    <p>@@number</p>\r\n}\r\n</script></div>\r\n<div id=\"sql_loops_foreach\" hidden></div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n","created":"2025-04-25T06:25:06","changed":"2025-05-08T08:33:21.6107561Z","test_parameters":null,"included_js_libs":"legacy_chartjs"}